article.headline: Southeast Missouri State 78, UC Riverside 75
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Michael Rembert scored 15 points and pulled down nine rebounds to help lead Southeast Missouri State over University of California-Riverside 78-75 on Friday. After getting down early 41-32, UCR (3-4) hit four straight 3-pointers to come back to within 48-45 at the half. The Redhawks (2-3) eventually gave up the lead with 12:49 to go in the game when UCR's Larry Cunningham hit a 3-pointer to bring the score to 56-54. Southeast fought back, and after a steal and dunk by David Johnson, led 73-68 with 1:10 to go. After a missed jumper by the Highlanders, Johnson hit a lay-up to add to the lead. However, UCR again came storming back, hitting two more 3-pointers to bringing UCR to within one with 15 seconds to play at 75-74. An intentional foul on the Highlanders' Charles Jim-George, however, sealed the victory for Southeast. Cunningham led three UCR players in double figures with 21 points, while Justin Bell added 18. Five players for Southeast scored in double figures, including Terrick Willoughby with 14 and Brandon Foust with 13.
